{"lemma":"ضِرُّ","slug":"ضِرُّ","root":"ض.ر.ر","root_slug":"ض-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضِرُّ","root":"ضرر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":19},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25664","n25666","n25665"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to harm, to damage","examples":[{"text":"أَنْتَ حُرٌّ مَا لَمْ تَضُرَّ.","english":"You are free as long as you do not harm."},{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ آمَنُوا عَلَيْكُمْ أَنفُسَكُمْ ۖ لَا يَضُرُّكُم مَّن ضَلَّ إِذَا ٱهْتَدَيْتُمْ ۚ إِلَى ٱللَّٰهِ مَرْجِعُكُمْ جَمِيعًا فَيُنَبِّئُكُم بِمَا كُنتُمْ تَعْمَلُونَ","english":"You who believe, you are responsible for your own souls; if anyone else goes astray it will not harm you so long as you follow the guidance; you will all return to God, and He will make you realize what you have done."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become blind (ضَرِير (ḍarīr))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَرَّ (ḍarra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calamity, damage, loss, harm, hurt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bodily affliction, leanness"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25664","headword_ar":"ضَرٌّ","root":"Dr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25666","headword_ar":"ضَرٌّ","root":"Dr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking a wife in addition to another wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~apN","text_ar":"ضَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukiHati AlmaroA^apu EalaY Dir~K","text_ar":"نُكِحَتِ المَرْاَةُ عَلَى ضِرٍّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman was taken to wife in addition to a former wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And, accord. to Aboo-'Abd-Allah Et-Tuwál,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazaw~ajotu","text_ar":"تَزَوَّجْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaroA^apa EalaY Dir~K","text_ar":"المَرْاَةَ عَلَى ضِرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dur~K","text_ar":"ضُرٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took the woman to wife in addition to another wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazaw~aja","text_ar":"تَزَوَّجَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Dir~K","text_ar":"عَلَى ضِرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dur~K","text_ar":"ضُرٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDaAr~apK","text_ar":"مُضَارَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He married so as to have two"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three wives together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And Kr mentions the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazaw~ajotu AlmaroA^apa EalaY","text_ar":"تَزَوَّجْتُ المَرْاَةَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dir~K kun~a lahaA","text_ar":"ضِرٍّ كُنَّ لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took to wife the woman in addition to others who were her fellow-wives"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and if it be so,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dir~","text_ar":"ضِرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. [used in this instance as an epithet, and therefore applicable to a pl. number as well as to a single person], formed by the rejection of the augmentative letter [in its verb, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDar~a","text_ar":"اَضَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or it is a pl. that has no sing. (TA.)       -A2-  One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN Dir~u A^aDoraArK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ضِرُّ اَضْرَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man"},{"kind":"text","text":"[who is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong one of strong ones;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~u A^aSolaAlK","text_ar":"صِلُّ اَصْلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dil~u A^aDolaAlK","text_ar":"ضِلُّ اَضْلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very cunning"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapN","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25665","headword_ar":"ضُرٌّ","root":"Dr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Harm, injury, hurt, mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"damage; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoEN","text_ar":"نَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~N","text_ar":"ضَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) or this is an inf. n., (S, Msb, K,) and the former is a simple subst.; (ADk, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DararN","text_ar":"ضَرَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is now the most common]: (S, Mgh, Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ADk, T, S, L, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DararN","text_ar":"ضَرَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDir~apN","text_ar":"تَضِرَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDur~apN","text_ar":"تَضُرَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K; for the right reading in the K is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAlD~araru suwo'u","text_ar":"والضَّرَرُ سُوْءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAli","text_ar":"الحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the L, &c.; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAlDrr wsw' AlHAl","text_ar":"والضرر وسوء الحال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; TA; [but in some of the copies of the K, and in the TA, this signification is assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~N","text_ar":"ضَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dur~N","text_ar":"ضُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the latter, its pl. is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDur~N","text_ar":"اَضُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodily affliction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoEN","text_ar":"نَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~N","text_ar":"ضَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h: (ADk, T, Msb, TA: *) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~apN","text_ar":"ضَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DararN","text_ar":"ضَرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~aA='u","text_ar":"ضَرَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaruwrapN","text_ar":"ضَرُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAruwraA='u","text_ar":"ضَارُورَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", all of which have similar meanings:] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) thus in the Kur xxi. 83: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leanness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of him who is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dariyr","text_ar":"ضَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)       -A2-  See also the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","Msb","Mgh","TA"]}]}}